from kimatum hiroki kimatum subject re open letter to nissan in smorri steven a morri write hey nissan why be you guy make any station wagon you use to make a wagon on every platform sentra stanza maxima and now none at all in fact they make some but they just do sell them here in sunny californium be a wagon base on sentra avenil be a wagon it look like infinity but actually it independently design to be a mean it not base on any sedan nissan have better consider to sell them here after buy my se-r and really love it i would like to buy another nissan product for my wife but prefer a wagon i own minivan and do prefer them how about an altima wagon or a sentra wagon would do sound nice but i doubt they have a plan coz avenil wa introduce to replace any sedan base wagon or here an even better suggestion why do you guy go ahead and buy the rest of fuji heavy industry subaru and put either an in-line or into the legacy wagon i buy the legacy in a minute if it have a nissan engine instead of the horizontal that they seem sentimentally attach to with all the camry accord tauru volvo and subaru wagon out there it get to be a market segment that would be worthwhile i can wait a year or two but if you do have something to compete by the model i may have to go elsewhere thank steve morri internet smorri addiction study pgm uucp uw-beaver uunet gtenmc dataio sumax smorri seattle university phone dept or direct seattle wa 